<div class="w-full h-full flex flex-col justify-center items-center overflow-y-auto">
    <x-card class="container lg:max-w-2xl mx-auto grid grid-cols-1 gap-2" shadow>
        <x-header title="About The Website" subtitle="Below are things to know about this website" separator />
        <div class="leading-loose tracking-widest indent-4 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 text-justify">
            <p><span class="font-semibold">File-Share</span> is a website that exists to store your <span class="font-semibold">Files</span> and <span class="font-semibold">share it</span> (if you want) to the world. <span class="font-semibold">The Files</span> are stored in <span class="font-semibold">Archive Box</span> and you can set the Archive Box to <span class="font-semibold">opened</span> or <span class="font-semibold">closed</span>, it means if the Archive Box is opened everyone can see and download the stored Files and if closed only the selected users can see and download the Files.</p>

            <p> The Archive Box has <span class="font-semibold">3 levels of permission</span>, and the levels are <span class="font-semibold">level 1</span> the user can only see and download the files, <span class="font-semibold">level 2</span> the user can see, download, store, and edit the files, <span class="font-semibold">level 3</span> the user can see, download, store, edit, and delete the files and also can give the other users a permission or change their permission, edit the Archive Box, and delete the Archive Box.</p>

            <p>Each users can create <span class="font-semibold">many</span> Archive Boxes, once the Archive Box <span class="font-semibold">created</span> they will get permission <span class="font-semibold">level 3</span> to <span class="font-semibold">manage</span> those Archive Boxes. The user with permission level 3 can give other user permission from level 1 to 3 <span class="font-semibold">(be careful permission level 3 is equal to owner of the Archive Box)</span>.</p>
        </div>
    </x-card>
</div>
